<Author>TramTourist
<Content>Close to the Airport but also to a busy rail line This hotel is about 10 minutes walk from Schoenfeld Airport and 5 minutes from the S-bahn station. Although I only stayed there 1 night, I found it clean and efficient although possibly lacking in charm and cosiness. The room I was given was very comfortable and well furnished, but there was no air conditioning, which could be a problem during the summer as the hotel is right next to a busy rail line which you can't ignore if the windows are open !There is a restaurant next door and a filling station with a shop just up the road, but very little else of interest (the area seemed to be mainly business, rather than residential).If you need to catch an early morning flight or will be flying into Schoenfeld late in the evening, then the Albergo is ideal for an overnight stay. However for longer stays you could probably find something better located in central Berlin. 
