<Author>Sabahanne
<Content>Very convenient hotel, no complaints I booked into the Albergo Berlin because I was a woman alone arriving on a late flight to Berlin Shoenefeld airport. All you have to do is just walk out to the main street in front of the airport, walk to the left for about 5 minutes and you are there. I got a very good rate on booking.com. The desk staff were lovely and helpful, the room was immaculately clean, and the breakfast buffet was great, as were the dining room staff. The rail station is opposite the airport so It is very simple to travel into the centre of Berlin, either by train or metro. On the train, you can reach Alexanderplatz in about 20 minutes, about 10 minutes longer to Zoologischer Garten. The metro may be quicker if one is pressed for time, but the train is a very enjoyable ride - clean, comfortable and uncrowded. 
