<Content>Dirty Albergo A 4 star hotel with a 1 star attitude. The room was dirty, with dirty floors and very dusty at higher levels. I wrote my name in the dust on the television in room 403 and added the date, I wonder how long it will be there! It cost us 9.40 euro for 2 x 75cl bottles of water. Breakfast was poor ,one you coukld associate with a low starred hotel. The waiting staff and the cleaning staff were functional whilst a good point was the reception staff who were very helpful. On arrival we were allowed to put our cases in the room which was not ready. However, we had noticed that the pillow cases needed changing as they were stained. When we came back that evening the room was made up and it was not until the following morning that we realised the pillow cases were the stained ones. We were allocated 1 bath towel and 2 hand towels and on our request this was changed but we ended up with 2 bath towels and 1 hand towel. The toilet seat was cracked underneath and the fitting was loose, the shower leaked onto the floor as the shower door did not fit correctly. 
