<Content>Albergo go go! I stayed here twice, on my way to and from Wolsztyn to drive steam trains. [That holiday was unbelievably brilliant, marred only by the dishonesty of the american travel agent, Rannoch and Howard Jones. You have no choice but to book through the latter as he has things all tied up with PKP (Polish Railways). My complaint including evidence and witnesses was ignored.See my review of the Wolsztyn Experience.]The Albergo was excellent apart from a language problem when I requested a cooked breakfast. This hotel could not be more convenient for Schoenefeld Airport and the Bahn. Food was good, staff were pleasant if very limited in use of English which made me use my schoolboy German, which was not a great help. Would definitely go again! 
