<Author>darkscot
<Content>Good for one night! If you know where this hotel is and don't have much luggage you can very easily walk to it from the airport. I didn't know how far it was and so took a taxi which cost 4euro and did not endear me to the driver. I arrived late (22:45) but the receptionist was friendly and helpful. The room was small, basically furnished and scruffy. It was also VERY hot which forced me to open the windows. After five minutes I found out how close it is to the S-Bahn line (VERY!). In spite of that i managed to sleep with the windows open even though there were trains all night.Breakfast was in a seperate building but only 30 seconds walk from reception. it was a typical German style buffet and very good indeed. Service was efficient and friendly. For the price and proximity to the airport I think this is excellent value for a one night stay. The only thing that let it down was the scruffiness of the rooms, they could do with re-decorating. 
