<Author>PurpleSprouting
<Content>Dont mention the war Arriving at the Hotel Albergo should have been easy. However a combination of two Reception staff with obvious personality bypasses and the fact that they did not seem to accept the computer Confirmation print-out as a booking hardly helped my opinion.After solving that, I went upto my hotel room. It was superbly clean,quite roomy (It was only me in the room!) The bathroom was white,functional and again spotless. Only complaint really is that the room was facing directly towards the main S-bahn line. However, double glazing soon solved that.Restaurant meals were lovely,well cooked and the staff I always found helpful. You were able to eat at the restaurant if you were a non-resident. It was Italian cookery which made a nice change from the norm.Hotel is only 500metres away from S-bahn Schonefeld which also links up with the airport (a short distance away). It only takes 15minutes to get into the city centre.Beware of the gym there were only 1 weights machine, one cycle, and a shoulder press when I was there! Also you have to pay for the sauna, a sum which was not mentioned when I booked online.Apart from that and the occasional sullen Reception staff I had a good stay.PS There is a live disco in the restaurant on a Saturday night which played Jive Bunny when I was there.....least said the better!! 
